social_posts.post_text: Barber asked to take a pic for her website and then told me I look like a Sad Boi™
Ending January on a high note. Very proud of myself for not crying.
Sarah Michelle Gellar now knows my name, and that gays call her “mother”. I have truly peaked.
We come to this place to scream. 📸: @cmaroon

Just found out that my pilot, KILL YOUR DARLINGS, has been selected to be featured in next month’s LGBTQ+ Los Angeles Film Festival! This script has such a special place in my heart, and I’m so excited to share it with the world. It’s a love letter to all the gay bars we lost during the pandemic, and follows the story of five East Side friends as they try to launch their queer-inclusive dance party and create a new safe space for the community… even if it means resorting to murder. Think Jennifer’s Body meets Jawbreaker, set in the world of Queer As Folk. A huge thank you to everybody who contributed to this process and read various drafts along the way, including @katierosereptar, @imuncharted, and @miri.smith — I owe y’all a drink. Meet me on the dance floor at next week’s Darling!
I have two years worth of moments I wish I could tell you about. I know you’re watching over me, still cheering me on. 💙
Happy birthday to the original party girl herself @cmcneil314. I love you more than baby uncle Kevin loves lucky charms.
March dump
Coachella Day 1, in which my tit was out for a majority of the afternoon and I got to hear Becky G sing Shower
Coachella Day 2 was brought to you by the Sistine Chapel, floral prints, and body-ody-ody 🎨🌹💪🏼 Thanks for welcoming us to your island, @charli_xcx 💜

Coachella Day 3 reminded me how much I love live music, dancing like a fool, and kissing my friends. My heart is so full and I’m ready to take the biggest nap imaginable. Until next time…💜✨🪩 

Also shoutout to @theambercrane for this stunning jumpsuit!
I love my friends because they’re always ready to commit to the bit.

Proud of my union for making the tough decision to strike. What we are asking for isn’t unreasonable. We refuse to let the studios turn our livelihood into a gig economy, and deny us the rights and proper compensation we have earned. I am scared. I am ready to fight. I am #WGAStrong.
Somehow, protesting feels good in a place like this. #WGAStrong
Went to the hottest club on Staten Island this weekend: the combination Communion/Christening party for Brian and Andrew. So glad I got to spend some time with the entire extended McNeil family.🩵✨

Dear AMPTP,

Joke’s on you! I love going for long walks, wooing at the top of my lungs, hanging out with my friends, and holding things in a manner that makes my arms look amazing. I can do this for the next 100 days and beyond. The first two weeks of the WGA Strike have been nothing short of inspiring, and reaffirmed how much I love being a union boy. We got this, y’all. #WGAstrong
In brightest day, in blackest night, no evil shall escape my sight. Let those who worship Zaslav’s might, beware our power, the writer’s strike!
Hi Barbie!

I have a lot of pride in my community, and I love getting to celebrate it with the people I love most. This year proved that even when things might seem shitty, you can never let that stop you from dancing. ❤️💜💙💚💛🧡

After three days of Pride and twelve consecutive hours of sleep, it’s time to get back to the picket lines for another week. Shoutout to everyone who’s been helping us keep the energy up as we enter into month two!

Week 6 ✅ 
Get some rest this weekend, y’all. We’ve got a long road ahead of us. 
📸: @j.w.hendricks

I remember reading about the ‘07-‘08 writer’s strike back when I was in high school, because I wanted to know why Pushing Daisies and Heroes weren’t coming back with new episodes after their fall finales. That’s when I first learned one day I might be able to join the @wgawest. And now here I am, 15 years later, standing with my union and fighting for the future of our industry. Hope that little nerd is proud of me today.

Still trying to wrap my head around the fact that I got my first Deadline mention in the middle of an ongoing strike, but I wanted to take a moment to celebrate the fact that Kill Your Darlings was chosen to be part of this year’s Out In Hollywood Out Loud list showcasing unproduced queer pilots. This script means the world to me, and I’m so thrilled to hear other people are enjoying it too. Thank you to everyone who listened to me pitch this idea time and time again, read countless drafts and gave extensive notes, and believed in me when I was at my lowest. You are all my Darlings, and I love you so much. ❤️💜💙💚💛
“How did I survive apocalyptic fire? I simply refused to feel the flames.” Nine weeks in and channeling my queen Emma Frost at the X-Men picket up at Disney.

My seventh Comic Con was also my shortest trip yet and I loved every moment of it. Seeing friends I haven’t run into in years and getting the chance to be surrounded by my fellow nerds will always be my favorite parts of this special weekend. Until next year, SDCC!
Come on, Oppie, let’s go party. We survived Barbenheimer 2k23.
Week 13 for the WGA on the picket lines, and I figured it was time to bust out one of my all time favorite karaoke songs. I can’t tell if I’ve fully gone mental or if this is peak me.
Spent most of July in a Speedo. Not mad about it. But also need more money for new speedos so let’s end this strike soon please.

100 days. An emotional milestone for all of us out here on the picket lines, fighting for a fair deal from the studios that continue to make billions of dollars from our collective countless hours of labor. 100 days of anger, anxiety, tears, sweat, panic attacks… but also 100 days of solidarity, reunions, dancing, chanting, and most importantly, community. We are stronger together, and we will not stop fighting until we are able to ensure a future for the working middle class of writers that keep this industry afloat. Thank you to every single person who has reached out along the way to show their support, whether it was through text, a home cooked meal, Venmos for the Dunkin fund, a shoulder to cry on, movie nights, or just a friend to talk to. You’re the reason I’ve been able to fighting the good fight. 💙✊🏼

100 Days long, 100 Days strong. Thrilled I got to have my Glee moment outside of the Paramount lot thanks to @picketlinekaraoke. Thanks for doing what y’all do to keep morale up to ensure these studios can’t rain on our parade. 💙✊🏼
16 weeks on strike and I haven’t even reached my final form yet. The AMPTP better be scared.

Heading into Week 17 like 🤪✊🏼⛈️🍤🪧🆒🏴‍☠️

📸: @j.w.hendricks
The Fraternal Order of RAS
DJ XSSY sets are my safe space

19 weeks without a fair deal, and the AMPTP refusing to negotiate in good faith. They’ve tried to divide us, they’ve tried to break us, but all they’ve done is make us stronger and more unified than ever. We won’t back down, because we know we’re on the right side of history.

Instead I wrote a song/I feel much better now 
📸: @sauvignonblancpink
Day 144. Team Paramount knows how to throw a good dance party.

That’s a wrap on yet another season of The Neil McNeil Show. This past year has been one of the most challenging and rewarding experiences, and I am so grateful for single every person who has filled my life with so much love, support, and strength throughout all this madness.
When two birthday queens come together to MAXimise their joint slay. Thank you to everyone who made yesterday’s celebration a day I will truly never forget.

“Jeannie in a bikini.”
“Scott in a Speedo.”
“Heh. Who could say no to that?”

Tattoo number 13 is dedicated to my all time favorite (and messiest) throuple in the comic book universe: Jean Grey, Cyclops, and Wolverine. In a recent episode of @cerebrocast, Johnathan Hickman was asked point blank if this was relationship was finally canon. He responded by saying that when he pitched the Krakoan era soft-reboot, he wanted “everyone to be fucking,” and Marvel let him run with it. So now these three share a conjoined bedroom on the Moon, and can be the happy polyamorous unit they were always meant to be. Love comes in many forms, and sometimes the only solution for a love triangle is for everyone to kiss.

Girl, the strike! (is over)

148 Days later, and we finally got the deal we deserved. I’m so incredibly proud of all of my fellow Guild members who continued to show up and never backed down. We did this together. And SAG-AFTRA, y’all are next! Ready to stand alongside y’all until the very end.
Ratification day got me feeling like. Congrats to all of my fellow WGA members who held the line for the past 5 months. Y’all are pretty exceptional.

Happy National Coming Out Day to this overly-confident teenager who wore this shirt during Spirit Week for Team Tuesday. Whether you’ve been out for five minutes or five decades, or if you’re still not ready to speak those words out loud, today is for you. Your community is here for you, and we are so happy you exist.

RIP Spider-Cube (October 20, 2023 - October 26, 2023)
No patch can erase your legacy in the Spider-Verse. Earth-1048 won’t be the same without you. 🕷️⬜️
“Power isn’t determined by your size, but by the size of your heart and your dreams.” ☠️👒
Disco never died 🔪 🪩
New York dump, hung out with a bunch of cute babies🗽✨🎅🏼
2023 was a shit show, but no matter how bad things got, I never stopped dancing. Big thanks to everyone who kept me going.
🎶 And a Happy Goon Year 🎶
